### The IPython approach

Bokeh leverages the **IPython / Jupyter display** and **ipykernel communication** method for dynimcally changing existing plots:

*Jupyter Javascript:*

```javascript
    Jupyter.notebook.kernel.comm_manager.register_target("nvd3_stat", function(comm, msg) {

        console.log("Comm for nvd3_stat opened");        // (1)

        comm.on_msg(function(msg) {
            console.log("handling sent message", msg)    // (2)
        });

        comm.on_close(function(msg) {
            console.log("Comm for nvd3_stat closed ", msg);         
        });    
    })
```

*Jupyter Python:*

```python
    comm = Comm(target_name='nvd3_stat', data={'event': 'open'})  # open the communication, (1) above will fire

    comm.send({"msg":msg})                                        # send a message to javascript, (2) above will fire
```
